                            <comment id="15247054" author="carp84" created="Tue, 19 Apr 2016 02:53:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching a screen shot of what we&apos;re using online to display what it will look like after the change, will attach the patch later&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15247262" author="carp84" created="Tue, 19 Apr 2016 06:42:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The initial patch&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15247272" author="eclark" created="Tue, 19 Apr 2016 06:53:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Totals are usually at the bottom of a table. I would expect averages to be in the headers.&lt;br/&gt;
Is it possible to do the sorting without using check boxes? That seems pretty unaesthetic ( not that my designs are picassos ).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15247724" author="carp84" created="Tue, 19 Apr 2016 13:12:47 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Totals are usually at the bottom of a table. I would expect averages to be in the headers.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In our case we care more about the totals and compute the average manually (region number is included in the &quot;Name&quot; header). And if there&apos;re hundreds of regions and totals at the bottom, it&apos;s kind of hard to be noticed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Is it possible to do the sorting without using check boxes? That seems pretty unaesthetic&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sorry but I don&apos;t quite catch you sir... The check boxes are for choosing ascending/descending-order and whether to display detailed region-name/start/end-key, and there&apos;s a &lt;tt&gt;Reorder&lt;/tt&gt; button to trigger the reorder. Maybe I didn&apos;t set any margin so it looked a little bit confusing, let me do some minor update, and please let me know if you still find it unaesthetic. (And with some suggestions please, I&apos;m really not that familiar with the front-end things (smile)).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15247732" author="carp84" created="Tue, 19 Apr 2016 13:17:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Minor refinement &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15248985" author="stack" created="Wed, 20 Apr 2016 00:06:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll take it. Looks great. I&apos;m +1 but get one from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=eclark&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;eclark&quot;&gt;Elliott Clark&lt;/a&gt; and I&apos;ll commit.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15249064" author="enis" created="Wed, 20 Apr 2016 01:05:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;can we change &quot;fileNum&quot; and totalFileNum to be storeFileCount or fileCount. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;regionSize should be storeFileSize? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15249151" author="carp84" created="Wed, 20 Apr 2016 02:42:34 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;can we change &quot;fileNum&quot; and totalFileNum to be storeFileCount or fileCount&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sure, let me change it to fileCount and totalStoreFileCount&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;regionSize should be storeFileSize?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a sum of all store file size under a region, so I guess regionSize is more accurate?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15249168" author="carp84" created="Wed, 20 Apr 2016 02:55:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Minor change, FileNum=&amp;gt;FileCount&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15250300" author="enis" created="Wed, 20 Apr 2016 17:18:43 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;This is a sum of all store file size under a region, so I guess regionSize is more accurate?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In metrics, we have storeFileSize, and regionSize as two different things. regionSize = storeFileSize + memstoreSize. Let&apos;s keep it consistent between the UI and metrics. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15250440" author="eclark" created="Wed, 20 Apr 2016 18:20:44 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;The check boxes are for choosing ascending/descending-order and whether to display detailed region-name/start/end-key, and there&apos;s a&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;My thought was that re-ordering is usually handled with an on click handler for the headers. Then you display either an up or down arrow on the header. Similar to this: &lt;a href=&quot;http://issues.wenzhixin.net.cn/bootstrap-table/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://issues.wenzhixin.net.cn/bootstrap-table/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15250900" author="easyliangjob" created="Wed, 20 Apr 2016 23:06:20 +0000"  >
&lt;p&gt;   I think it is good idea to put more details about regions on table.jsp. But I have some concerns and ideas.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    (1) The same information on table.jsp should be consistent among all the webpages, for example: for the &quot;FileNum&quot; info on your screenshot. On the Regions on the region server UI: it uses &quot;Num. Storefile&quot;(see attached screenshot).&lt;br/&gt;
     (2) It is a little crowded if you put all the information on same lines on one page.&lt;br/&gt;
     (3) The UI style should be consistent (Master UI and region server UI)&lt;br/&gt;
         The region server UI uses &apos;tab&apos; for displaying different details. For example, &apos;Base Info&apos;, &apos;Request metrics&apos;, &apos;Storefile metrics&apos;. I attached a screenshot about the design of this &quot;tab&quot; on the existing region server UI page and you can take a look.  This &apos;tab&apos; can make the page not so crowded.&lt;/p&gt;


</comment>
                            <comment id="15251662" author="carp84" created="Thu, 21 Apr 2016 10:07:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry, this is really not where my expertise lies in... Maybe we could first commit and make the function available, then let experts do the refinements on the style? Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15251664" author="carp84" created="Thu, 21 Apr 2016 10:09:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I see, makes sense. Let me update the patch. Thanks for the clarification sir &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=enis&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;enis&quot;&gt;Enis Soztutar&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15251681" author="carp84" created="Thu, 21 Apr 2016 10:27:35 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;The same information on table.jsp should be consistent among all the webpages&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Makes sense, let me do some updates to keep name consistency&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;It is a little crowded if you put all the information on same lines on one page.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I guess it looks fine from the screen shot? I&apos;m not an expert at front-end things, so I&apos;d like to focus on function instead of display style in this JIRA. Please feel free to open JIRAs to improve it after the function is there. Or IMHO maybe the principle here is that simple but useful pages are enough? Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;The UI style should be consistent (Master UI and region server UI)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I think this is true, and welcome to open another JIRA improve/discuss about this. Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15257760" author="carp84" created="Tue, 26 Apr 2016 08:48:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Update patch according to review comments, and attach screenshot of the latest page.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=enis&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;enis&quot;&gt;Enis Soztutar&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=eclark&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;eclark&quot;&gt;Elliott Clark&lt;/a&gt;, mind review again? Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15263423" author="carp84" created="Fri, 29 Apr 2016 02:24:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ping &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=stack&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;stack&quot;&gt;stack&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=enis&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;enis&quot;&gt;Enis Soztutar&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=eclark&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;eclark&quot;&gt;Elliott Clark&lt;/a&gt;, ok for me to commit this one? Will wait for one more day and get it in if no objections, thanks. &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15264322" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Fri, 29 Apr 2016 16:48:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Took a look at new_table_jsp_v3.png - it looks good.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15264352" author="eclark" created="Fri, 29 Apr 2016 17:11:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks good enough. Lets file a jira to make the headers the sorter and then I&apos;m good with it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15268628" author="carp84" created="Tue, 3 May 2016 12:35:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Have created &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-15758&quot; title=&quot;Make headers the sorter for region details on table.jsp&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-15758&quot;&gt;HBASE-15758&lt;/a&gt; for the &quot;sort on headers&quot; task. Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15268630" author="carp84" created="Tue, 3 May 2016 12:36:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;the v5 patch did a small refactor after &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-15607&quot; title=&quot;Remove PB references from Admin for 2.0&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-15607&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-15607&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, and upload patch for branch-1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15268633" author="carp84" created="Tue, 3 May 2016 12:38:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Pushed into master and branch-1. Thanks all for review &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=eclark&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;eclark&quot;&gt;Elliott Clark&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=stack&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;stack&quot;&gt;stack&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=enis&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;enis&quot;&gt;Enis Soztutar&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tedyu&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tedyu&quot;&gt;Ted Yu&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
